            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">This Collection details Lewis Myer’s experiences and recollections during World War II which he was drafted into the United States Army in 1944. As a member of the 2nd Division, 38th Infantry, he served in France, Germany and Czechoslovakia. The Collection contains personal service records, a hand drawn map and photographs. Dating from 1944 thru 1946,and oral history interview conducted on 2005.</abstract>
